text:
state-worlds is confusing atm because FTC just changed their rules.  But by default, each region (state) gets to send 2 teams to worlds, 1st place ranking in state and 1st place Inspire Award winner, although additional spots may be given to larger regions (which might include us, not entirely sure).

for interleagues-state, afaik (and more exp people & mr peck can correct any details i got wrong) 4 teams advance to state from each interleague, those being the top 2 ranked at interleagues and Inspire Award 1st and 2nd place
